{
  "text": "Taylor et al. [CITATION_1] undertook a laboratory study to determine the rate and quantity of leaching loss from aspen wood, the chemical composition of the leachate, and the strength and persistence of leachate toxicity. In that study, leachate from aspen wood chips (9:1 w/w ratio of water to wood) was characterized by low pH, high conductivity, and very high BOD, leading to persistent anoxia. The leachate was rich in phenols and organic carbon, and it was lethal to fish and invertebrates at very low concentrations.",
  "correct_citation": {
